\f[B]Fenced Divs\f[R]: Pandoc\-style fenced divs with block type support.
Use \f[CR]>blocktype\f[R] syntax to create different HTML elements
(e.g., \f[CR]::: >aside {.sidebar}\f[R] creates \f[CR]<aside>\f[R]
instead of \f[CR]<div>\f[R]).
Common block types include \f[CR]aside\f[R], \f[CR]article\f[R],
\f[CR]section\f[R], \f[CR]details\f[R], \f[CR]summary\f[R],
\f[CR]header\f[R], \f[CR]footer\f[R], \f[CR]nav\f[R], and custom
elements.
Available in unified mode.
